******
[1] Cambodia
Date: Thu 2 Jun 2016
Source: Xinhuanet [edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2016-06/02/c_135407427.htm


Cambodia on Thu [2 Jun 2016] confirmed the 3rd case of measles so far this year [2016] after the World Health Organization (WHO) declared in March last year [2015] that the South East Asian country was measles-free.

The new case was detected in a 1 year old infant who was admitted to the National Pediatric Hospital in Phnom Penh last month [May 2016], said a joint statement released by the Cambodian Ministry of Health and WHO. "The suspected case was confirmed as measles by the National Institute of Public Health, and, subsequently, it was confirmed by the WHO Regional Reference Laboratory in (China's) Hong Kong on 21 May 2016," the statement said. "So far this year [2016], 3 cases of measles were found in Cambodia after the 1st 2 cases were confirmed in January [2016]," it continued.

After receiving the laboratory results, the Ministry of Health has sent a team of health experts to look further into the new case in order to prepare for any urgent response, the statement added. "For this new case of measles, we have immediately launched an inspection and will take all necessary measures, including vaccination, to stop the transmission of the virus," Health Minister Mam Bunheng said.

