******
[4] USA (Arizona)
Date: Tue 7 Jun 2016
Source: 12 News [edited]
http://www.12news.com/news/local/arizona/new-case-of-measles-reported-in-maricopa-county-14-total/235619135


The Arizona Department of Health Services has confirmed a new case of measles, bringing the total to 14 cases. The newest case is a resident who lives in Maricopa County and has ties to the private detention facility in Eloy. 13 of the confirmed cases have been in Pinal County, with one case reported in Maricopa County.

Health experts say that 9 out of 10 people who aren't vaccinated will become infected with measles. The virus can linger in the air for 2 hours after an infected person leaves the room. It's especially dangerous for the young, elderly, and people with compromised immune systems.

